A vehicle with the registration number, KSF 383 XZ, on Wednesday, crushed a Lagos Waste Management Authority employee on duty at Anthony Bus Stop in Lagos State. It was gathered that the woman died on the spot and her remains had been taken to the mortuary. The State Traffic Officer, CSP Oriyomi Oluwasanmi, confirmed the incident and said she was at the scene to stem any possible crisis. She said the Divisional Traffic Officer called her attention when those at the scene of the accident did not allow the vehicle to be towed. She added that the accident disrupted the flow of traffic for those on essential duties. Meanwhile, an official of LAWMA, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said that the woman was carrying out official duty when the utility vehicle reversed on the highway and crushed her to death. According to the official, the driver missed the service lane that could take him to Oshodi and was trying to reverse when the accident occurred. (NAN)